1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 20=

3
00:01:39,470 --> 00:01:41,040
This is the chat record
between the plaintiff

4
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:43,760
(Chat History with Brother)
and the defendant on WeChat.

5
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:49,240
The insurance premium was to be paid
from our dad's pension.

6
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:51,639
I heard you argued fiercely
about it before.

7
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:53,840
I thought you paid for it yourselves.

8
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:56,070
So in the end,
it all came out of Dad's money.

9
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:58,430
Defendant's counsel, watch your wording.

10
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:00,840
You didn't contribute a single cent,

11
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:03,760
nor did you pay my client anything.

12
00:02:03,830 --> 00:02:06,200
So what do

13
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:07,760
these chat records prove?

14
00:02:08,070 --> 00:02:09,589
You are siblings,

15
00:02:09,590 --> 00:02:11,559
not an employer and employee.

16
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:13,719
What, did you
even sign a labor contract?

17
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:14,879
If there really was a contract,

18
00:02:14,880 --> 00:02:17,230
you could file a lawsuit
with the civil division.

19
00:02:18,070 --> 00:02:19,510
Don't worry, Miss.

20
00:02:20,030 --> 00:02:22,230
If they want to sue, let them.

21
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,159
I'll represent you
for free in this case.

22
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:25,309
Please don't twist the facts.

23
00:02:25,310 --> 00:02:25,999
Right.

24
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,069
We never mentioned any contract.

25
00:02:28,070 --> 00:02:29,910
We only want to prove

26
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,679
that Lu Huilan

27
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:33,069
is very muddle-headed.

28
00:02:33,070 --> 00:02:35,189
She intended to pocket
our dad's pension.

29
00:02:35,190 --> 00:02:36,589
She bears responsibility

30
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:37,719
for our dad's death.

31
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:38,910
A great deal of responsibility.

32
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,440
These are Lu Huilan's account records
from the past month.

33
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:43,040
Out-of-pocket medicine
not covered by insurance,

34
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:44,440
820 yuan per month.

35
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:47,029
Taking the old man
to physical therapy, 80 each time,

36
00:02:47,030 --> 00:02:48,239
320 a month.

37
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:50,350
Food, communication,

38
00:02:50,510 --> 00:02:52,200
everything costs money.

39
00:02:52,470 --> 00:02:54,280
At least three
to four thousand every month.

40
00:02:54,350 --> 00:02:55,880
In winter and summer,

41
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,789
when elderly illnesses are more common,

42
00:02:57,790 --> 00:02:59,879
it can reach seven
to eight thousand a month.

43
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:02,509
But your father's monthly pension
is only three to four thousand.

44
00:03:02,510 --> 00:03:03,439
So tell me,

45
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:04,910
what exactly did she embezzle?

46
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,309
Wait.

47
00:03:06,310 --> 00:03:07,559
Lu Huilan,

48
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:10,719
don't try to fool us
just because the print is small.

49
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:12,880
You claim all the money
was spent on Dad.

50
00:03:13,510 --> 00:03:15,320
Then, what about the movie tickets?

51
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:16,689
You seemed pretty relaxed.

52
00:03:16,689 --> 00:03:18,440
(Life Services, Movie Ticket)
Still had time to watch movies?

53
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:19,320
Yes!

54
00:03:19,350 --> 00:03:20,390
Brother,

55
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:24,069
that's Dad's only hobby.

56
00:03:24,070 --> 00:03:25,879
What's wrong with him

57
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:28,070
watching a movie using his own pension?

58
00:03:28,630 --> 00:03:31,160
That was Dad's pension.

59
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:33,029
Yes.

60
00:03:33,030 --> 00:03:35,880
That pension could have
been used to buy insurance

61
00:03:36,630 --> 00:03:39,510
so that after Dad passed,
there would be a large payout.

62
00:03:39,750 --> 00:03:42,670
What does that have to do with Dad?

63
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:45,349
I just wanted to use that money

64
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:47,720
to buy him some good food

65
00:03:48,190 --> 00:03:49,910
and get him some clothes.

66
00:03:51,310 --> 00:03:54,189
I took him out for walks,
to watch movies,

67
00:03:54,190 --> 00:03:56,439
and to stroll in the park.

68
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,789
Don't even mention going to the park.

69
00:03:57,790 --> 00:03:59,510
Just thinking about it makes me angry.

70
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,399
Last winter,

71
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,069
remember how bad Dad's fever got?

72
00:04:02,070 --> 00:04:02,959
In the dead of winter,

73
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,509
you still took him to the park.

74
00:04:04,510 --> 00:04:06,790
Wasn't that because of you?

75
00:04:07,030 --> 00:04:09,440
He had been cooped up all winter.

76
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:12,790
Finally, there was a sunny day,

77
00:04:13,030 --> 00:04:14,910
and he wanted to go out for a walk.

78
00:04:15,950 --> 00:04:17,710
And last summer,

79
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,039
Dad had diarrhea

80
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:21,189
after eating the breakfast you made.

81
00:04:21,190 --> 00:04:22,359
Why?

82
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,829
Didn't you use leftover rice

83
00:04:23,830 --> 00:04:24,799
to cook porridge for him?

84
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:26,000
Do you admit it?

85
00:04:26,310 --> 00:04:28,509
- Is that how you take care of Dad?
- That's outrageous.

86
00:04:28,510 --> 00:04:29,599
Isn't this just a typical case of

87
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:31,710
the more you do,
the more mistakes you make?

88
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:33,559
A good horse dies on the battlefield,

89
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:35,389
a good car eventually rattles.

90
00:04:35,390 --> 00:04:37,389
Why can an idiot
live ten thousand years?

91
00:04:37,390 --> 00:04:39,709
Because it hides in its shell
and does nothing.

92
00:04:39,710 --> 00:04:40,039
Hey,

93
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:41,309
who are you calling that?

94
00:04:41,310 --> 00:04:43,039
Your Honor,
this lawyer is insulting people.

95
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:44,830
Yes, he's insulting us.

96
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:48,189
Defendant's counsel,

97
00:04:48,190 --> 00:04:50,189
do you have any new evidence to submit?

98
00:04:50,190 --> 00:04:51,800
I have here

99
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,849
witness statements from neighbors,

100
00:04:53,850 --> 00:04:55,119
as well as a joint letter

101
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:56,760
signed by 32 relatives and friends.

102
00:04:57,880 --> 00:04:59,239
These fully prove

103
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,309
that my client,

104
00:05:00,310 --> 00:05:01,119
Lu Huilan,

105
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:04,309
took meticulous care
of the deceased during his lifetime.

106
00:05:04,310 --> 00:05:07,510
She is a very warm and devoted daughter.

107
00:05:07,710 --> 00:05:08,629
That's enough.

108
00:05:08,630 --> 00:05:10,149
You're just trying to play

109
00:05:10,150 --> 00:05:11,799
the "no achievement,
but effort counts" card.

110
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:12,749
That's right.

111
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:14,120
Forget it.

112
00:05:14,190 --> 00:05:16,470
The court's time is valuable.

113
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,389
Your Honor,

114
00:05:17,390 --> 00:05:18,630
I believe

115
00:05:18,710 --> 00:05:20,710
this supporting material
is very important.

116
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:21,389
Please...

117
00:05:21,390 --> 00:05:22,119
That's enough.

118
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:23,149
These matters

119
00:05:23,150 --> 00:05:24,679
have already been largely addressed

120
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:26,510
in previous hearings.

121
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:29,749
If there is no new evidence, this court will
proceed to deliver the judgment.

122
00:05:29,750 --> 00:05:30,920
Now?

123
00:05:31,070 --> 00:05:32,560
All rise.

124
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:33,599
That fast?

125
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,710
Yeah.

126
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,879
Lu Guangyou and Lu Aimin

127
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:41,389
versus Lu Huilan,
inheritance dispute case,

128
00:05:41,390 --> 00:05:43,069
this court rules as follows.

129
00:05:43,070 --> 00:05:43,799
First,

130
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:44,829
the deceased, Lu Jianguo,

131
00:05:44,830 --> 00:05:46,599
left cash savings totaling

132
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,599
32,890 yuan.

133
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:51,599
To be inherited by the eldest son,
Lu Guangyou, and the second son, Lu Aimin,

134
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,389
each receiving one-half,

135
00:05:53,390 --> 00:05:56,680
that is, 16,445 yuan per person.

136
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:57,829
Second,

137
00:05:57,830 --> 00:06:00,509
the golden retriever pet dog
raised by Lu Jianguo during his lifetime

138
00:06:00,510 --> 00:06:02,560
shall belong to
his third daughter, Lu Huilan.

139
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:04,039
Third,

140
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:06,309
the property located
at North Third Lane, Qingcheng District,

141
00:06:06,310 --> 00:06:08,559
in Jiatai Residential Complex,
a two-bedroom apartment,

142
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:10,479
with a floor area of 83 square meters,

143
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:12,439
shall be jointly inherited
by the two sons and one daughter.

144
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:13,999
Among them, the eldest son Lu Guangyou,

145
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,800
having fulfilled less filial support
obligation during his father's lifetime,

146
00:06:16,950 --> 00:06:20,359
is awarded a 15 percent share.

147
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,320
What?

148
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:23,030
That's not right.

149
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,560
The second son, Lu Aimin,

150
00:06:25,830 --> 00:06:27,559
though living just across
the street from his father,

151
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:29,799
paid no attention
to his father's condition

152
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:32,069
and failed to fulfill his duties
of support as a son.

153
00:06:32,070 --> 00:06:33,999
This court awards him

154
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,679
a 15 percent share.

155
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:37,630
How did I fail in my duties?

156
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:39,629
I paid 800 yuan a month in support.

157
00:06:39,630 --> 00:06:41,320
Did I ever miss a cent?

158
00:06:41,950 --> 00:06:44,479
This is a wrongful judgment.

159
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:46,470
This is completely arbitrary.

160
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,949
You said I didn't care about my father?

161
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:49,799
Ask her.

162
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,239
Last year at the central park,

163
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:52,119
when I took my dad out,

164
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,799
didn't I help him open his thermos

165
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:54,879
and tuck in his blanket?

166
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:57,239
These are details you don't see.

167
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:59,470
Plaintiffs, please maintain order.

168
00:06:59,950 --> 00:07:02,149
Lu Huilan, as the youngest daughter
of the deceased,

169
00:07:02,150 --> 00:07:05,030
devoted herself to caring for
her bedridden father for seven years.

170
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:07,040
During that time, she was widely
praised by relatives, friends,

171
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:09,039
doctors, and neighbors alike.

172
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,629
She fully embodied

173
00:07:10,630 --> 00:07:12,760
the traditional virtue of filial piety
and respect for the elderly.

174
00:07:12,830 --> 00:07:13,829
This court rules

175
00:07:13,830 --> 00:07:16,879
that she shall inherit 70 percent
of the property left by her father.

176
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:17,829
Corrupt judge!

177
00:07:17,830 --> 00:07:19,949
I refuse to accept this.
I will file a complaint against you!

178
00:07:19,950 --> 00:07:21,119
I absolutely refuse.

179
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:23,269
You're just a basic-level court.

180
00:07:23,270 --> 00:07:24,999
- Your ruling doesn't count.
- Yes, I will appeal.

181
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,390
- I'll appeal.
- I'll appeal.

182
00:07:26,830 --> 00:07:28,309
Filing an appeal is your right.

183
00:07:28,310 --> 00:07:29,629
But let me remind you,

184
00:07:29,630 --> 00:07:31,599
you must file the appeal
within fifteen days

185
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,559
from the date you receive the judgment.

186
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:35,389
Otherwise, after fifteen days,

187
00:07:35,390 --> 00:07:37,030
this judgment
will take immediate effect.

188
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:38,470
No need to remind us.

189
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:42,710
Not bad, right?

190
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:45,360
Don't get too pleased with yourselves!

191
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:46,919
I will surely appeal!

192
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:48,039
Corrupt judge, I'll report you!

193
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:50,239
So the corrupt judge took bribes?

194
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,439
Corrupt judge!

195
00:07:51,440 --> 00:07:52,710
Impressive.

196
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:54,440
Really impressive.

197
00:07:57,630 --> 00:07:58,760
Miss,

198
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:00,309
we won the case.

199
00:08:00,310 --> 00:08:01,269
We won.

200
00:08:01,270 --> 00:08:03,359
Now I can finally answer to Ms. Qin.

201
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,439
Yes.

202
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:06,509
Please make sure
to thank Ms. Qin for me.

203
00:08:06,510 --> 00:08:08,070
Thanks to her for persuading me.

204
00:08:08,310 --> 00:08:09,800
And I should thank you too.

205
00:08:10,310 --> 00:08:12,389
- You're so busy.
- Go get back to your work first.

206
00:08:12,390 --> 00:08:14,360
Yet you still came to court for me.

207
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:16,709
Don't listen to Ms. Qin talking me up.

208
00:08:16,710 --> 00:08:17,829
What busy?

209
00:08:17,830 --> 00:08:19,389
I spend my days playing ball.

210
00:08:19,390 --> 00:08:20,239
It's Ms. Qin

211
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:22,000
holding the office together.

212
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:24,389
If she hadn't come to me
looking for a job back then,

213
00:08:24,390 --> 00:08:27,000
I would've shut it down
and retired long ago.

214
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,629
With her stirring things up,

215
00:08:28,630 --> 00:08:30,680
I get a bit of pocket money too.

216
00:08:30,830 --> 00:08:32,800
And guess what? After all her efforts,

217
00:08:33,030 --> 00:08:34,509
she's gotten me interested again.

218
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:35,629
If I shut it down,

219
00:08:35,630 --> 00:08:36,999
I'd feel reluctant.

220
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,509
Please don't close it.

221
00:08:38,510 --> 00:08:40,389
So many ordinary folks around here.

222
00:08:40,390 --> 00:08:41,879
If you shut this little office,

223
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:43,470
who would they turn to?

224
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:46,199
Look around here,

225
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:48,350
so many high-rise buildings.

226
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:50,149
But every time I see them,

227
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:52,040
I feel uneasy.

228
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:55,200
That day, luckily, I walked
into your small office

229
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:57,200
and met Ms. Qin.

230
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:59,400
Otherwise, I wouldn't have
made it this far.

231
00:08:59,790 --> 00:09:01,149
Alright, for what you just said,

232
00:09:01,150 --> 00:09:02,149
I won't close it.

233
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:03,920
I won't close it.

234
00:09:05,150 --> 00:09:07,320
By the way, I almost forgot,

235
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:11,110
please thank Judge Shu for me.

236
00:09:11,430 --> 00:09:13,479
I was completely overwhelmed in court.

237
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:16,110
No need, the judges all understand.

238
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:18,110
She's not doing it for your thanks.

239
00:09:19,670 --> 00:09:21,520
(Giving and fault)

240
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:23,359
(often leave the most uneven records)

241
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,560
(in the ledger of family ties.)

242
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:28,359
(Those daily acts of care and toil)

243
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,749
(are hard to measure)

244
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:31,959
(and are often, in the final reckoning,)

245
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:33,750
(easily forgotten.)

246
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,959
(And yet, out of helplessness,)

247
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:39,199
(a momentary mistake born of goodwill)

248
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:42,629
(may be magnified like a thunderclap,)

249
00:09:42,630 --> 00:09:45,200
(becoming evidence to deny everything.)

250
00:09:45,750 --> 00:09:48,750
(This forms one of the most helpless
paradoxes of human nature.)

251
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:50,879
(The more one gives,)

252
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:53,750
(the heavier the burden
of judgment they often bear.)

253
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:56,590
(When responsibility becomes a habit)

254
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:59,160
(and giving is taken for granted,)

255
00:09:59,430 --> 00:10:01,079
(any single accident)

256
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:04,470
(can erase years
of accumulated devotion.)

257
00:10:05,030 --> 00:10:06,879
(We are too used to judging outcomes)

258
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:09,040
(to retroactively condemn the process.)

259
00:10:09,270 --> 00:10:13,870
(The figure who quietly carried
the weight of the family over long years,)

260
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:16,479
(why is their worth so easily)

261
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:19,640
(negated by a single tragic accident?)

262
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:23,040
(When family ties are placed
under the spotlight of benefits)

263
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:25,959
(the law may decide
the ownership of property,)

264
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:28,479
(but what truly deserves
to be seen and cherished)

265
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:30,479
(is the quiet tenderness)

266
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:32,440
(ignored over the long passage of time.)

267
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:35,110
(What needs redemption)

268
00:10:35,150 --> 00:10:36,999
(is the truth of love after tragedy,)

269
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,429
(still hidden by notions
of right and wrong)

270
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:42,870
(and filled with
helplessness and scars.)

271
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:59,600
(Jindian Law Firm)

272
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:05,320
♪Rushing between buildings♪

273
00:11:06,660 --> 00:11:09,599
♪Caught in the grind of daily living♪

274
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:13,560
♪Facing the surging waves of life♪

275
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:18,570
♪Hearing the ticking
of a wound-up spring♪

276
00:11:18,580 --> 00:11:23,500
♪Ready to chase dreams
through sleepless nights♪

277
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:27,409
♪For the distant place we long to reach♪

278
00:11:27,410 --> 00:11:32,539
♪We must first go against the current♪

279
00:11:32,540 --> 00:11:36,499
♪I will step into the crowd♪

280
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:41,500
♪Unfolding a story
full of twists with courage♪

281
00:11:41,540 --> 00:11:45,469
♪Through wind and across rivers♪

282
00:11:45,470 --> 00:11:48,029
♪Even if the road
beneath my feet is winding♪

283
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:50,440
♪I still look ahead with hope♪

284
00:11:50,470 --> 00:11:54,349
♪I will run toward the future♪

285
00:11:54,350 --> 00:11:59,340
♪Sweeping away the dust between us♪

286
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:03,260
♪Searching for the warmth we had♪

287
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:08,300
♪Like a migrating flock♪

288
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:10,110
(I just want to cherish the present.)

289
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:12,440
(Jindian Law Firm)
(If we stop now,)

290
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:14,719
(every time we meet in the future,)

291
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:16,789
(we'll have to suppress
our feelings for each other,)

292
00:12:16,790 --> 00:12:18,230
(with nothing left but regret.)

293
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:22,680
(Jindian Law Firm)

294
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,200
Jing.

295
00:12:37,910 --> 00:12:40,269
Jing, you were amazing today.

296
00:12:40,270 --> 00:12:41,990
You're my idol.

297
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:45,239
Those two Lu brothers
must have lost their minds.

298
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:47,389
They actually had the nerve
to bring a case like this.

299
00:12:47,390 --> 00:12:48,909
When the defendant refused an autopsy,

300
00:12:48,910 --> 00:12:49,999
I thought we were done for.

301
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:53,269
The plaintiff would definitely
seize on that and blow it out of proportion.

302
00:12:53,270 --> 00:12:55,359
Good thing we found evidence

303
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:57,500
that the insurance premium
wasn't paid by them.

304
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:59,480
Otherwise, we would've had
to go to the First Civil Division

305
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:00,789
and fight another lawsuit.

306
00:13:00,790 --> 00:13:01,719
They might not

307
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:03,470
even intend
to pursue this case for real.

308
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:04,389
After all, whether Lu Huilan

309
00:13:04,390 --> 00:13:05,879
can come up with over 300,000,

310
00:13:05,880 --> 00:13:07,640
they know better than anyone.

311
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:09,239
Their real purpose

312
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:10,509
was to prove

313
00:13:10,510 --> 00:13:12,719
that Lu Huilan made repeated mistakes

314
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:13,789
while caring for their father.

315
00:13:13,790 --> 00:13:16,320
The more mistakes she made,
the less she would get.

316
00:13:17,790 --> 00:13:20,070
Do you know how close
it was at the start?

317
00:13:20,150 --> 00:13:21,029
I really thought

318
00:13:21,030 --> 00:13:23,909
Jing was going to accept
the plaintiff's claim.

319
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:25,999
I kept thinking, what if
the premium really was paid by them?

320
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,389
Then Lu Huilan, as the defendant,

321
00:13:27,390 --> 00:13:28,839
would be in serious trouble.

322
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:30,680
Luckily, it was just a scare.

323
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,549
In this case,

324
00:13:32,550 --> 00:13:34,389
what exactly caused the old man's death,

325
00:13:34,390 --> 00:13:36,110
whether the insurance
was even purchased,

326
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:37,509
and whose money was used to buy it,

327
00:13:37,510 --> 00:13:38,839
none of that really mattered.

328
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:40,029
Because from the very beginning,

329
00:13:40,030 --> 00:13:41,719
they were just being unreasonable.

330
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:42,999
When that angle didn't work,

331
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:45,479
they switched to making
an issue out of the insurance.

332
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:48,040
If we let that continue,
it would never end.

333
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:49,999
The more you do,
the more you're at fault.

334
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:52,040
That's always been the way.

335
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:53,789
No matter how many mistakes
Lu Huilan made,

336
00:13:53,790 --> 00:13:55,719
they were mistakes made
while fulfilling her filial duty.

337
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:57,879
But those two brothers are different.

338
00:13:57,880 --> 00:13:59,149
They did nothing at all,

339
00:13:59,150 --> 00:14:00,950
so naturally, they made no mistakes.

340
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:03,319
If I had agreed to their demands today

341
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:05,470
and stripped Lu Huilan
of her inheritance rights,

342
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:07,879
then in families with multiple children,

343
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:09,440
who would still step up
to care for the elderly?

344
00:14:09,510 --> 00:14:11,640
Wouldn't everyone just stand by

345
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:13,509
and wait to divide the inheritance?

346
00:14:13,510 --> 00:14:15,479
Exactly. Whoever takes responsibility
ends up hurt.

347
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,640
Those willing to care
would all be scared off.

348
00:14:18,030 --> 00:14:18,879
That's right.

349
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:19,959
Did you see

350
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:21,549
how those two brothers left?

351
00:14:21,550 --> 00:14:22,719
I think

352
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:24,269
there's no way they'll accept

353
00:14:24,270 --> 00:14:26,119
this outcome willingly.

354
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:27,350
If you ask me,

355
00:14:27,510 --> 00:14:29,160
they will either appeal

356
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:30,830
or file a complaint.

357
00:14:31,430 --> 00:14:32,319
And make a scene.

358
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:33,629
Let them.

359
00:14:33,630 --> 00:14:35,199
At worst, it'll affect my appeal rate.

360
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:37,839
The judges at the Intermediate People's Court
were raised by parents too.

361
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:38,629
I don't believe

362
00:14:38,630 --> 00:14:40,800
they would support
this kind of behavior.

363
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:42,070
That makes sense.

364
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:45,479
Kuang, where's Yu Le?

365
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:46,830
Why haven't I seen her?

366
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,160
Le?

367
00:14:48,270 --> 00:14:50,230
She went to pick up her "luxury lunch."

368
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:52,110
Luxury lunch?

369
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:54,070
She really lives the good life all day.

370
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:55,440
Then I'll head inside.

371
00:15:07,120 --> 00:15:08,239
Hello.

372
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:09,629
I'm here to onboard today.

373
00:15:09,630 --> 00:15:10,549
My name is Qin Rui.

374
00:15:10,550 --> 00:15:12,400
Hello, let me check for you.

375
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:15,070
Have a seat.

376
00:15:16,270 --> 00:15:18,029
How was your first day?

377
00:15:18,030 --> 00:15:18,909
Pretty good.

378
00:15:18,910 --> 00:15:21,230
I'll work hard to keep up with everyone.

379
00:15:22,390 --> 00:15:23,479
I think you know

380
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:25,599
the annual attrition rate
at Ronghe Law Firm.

381
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:27,230
If you want to stay,

382
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:29,280
hard work alone won't be enough.

383
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:31,839
As a lawyer,

384
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:33,560
your academic background
isn't as strong as theirs.

385
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:34,629
So I hope

386
00:15:34,630 --> 00:15:36,870
you can develop your own strengths.

387
00:15:37,550 --> 00:15:38,680
Strengths?

388
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:40,269
In my view,

389
00:15:40,270 --> 00:15:42,680
you're different from some
of the elite lawyers.

390
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:45,429
But I think that's exactly
your advantage.

391
00:15:45,430 --> 00:15:46,239
So I hope

392
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:48,870
you can blend these two styles together.

393
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:53,070
But I have to be upfront.

394
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:54,549
If your performance
isn't up to standard,

395
00:15:54,550 --> 00:15:56,320
I won't go easy on you.

396
00:15:58,910 --> 00:16:00,640
Have you read the contract I gave you?

397
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:01,479
Yes.

398
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:03,119
This is a contract from three years ago

399
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:05,680
for Jianqiang Group's
acquisition of Runyu.

400
00:16:05,750 --> 00:16:07,319
I noticed that some of the clauses

401
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:08,509
are relatively lenient.

402
00:16:08,510 --> 00:16:09,839
Especially the penalty clauses,

403
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:10,999
which are set at the minimum level.

404
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,429
But I also looked into it,

405
00:16:12,430 --> 00:16:14,839
Runyu was in high demand at the time.

406
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:16,269
Jianqiang Group
was willing to agree to this,

407
00:16:16,270 --> 00:16:18,789
probably to secure an early advantage.

408
00:16:18,790 --> 00:16:20,719
In simple terms,

409
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:22,990
keep your eyes open,
assess the situation,

410
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:24,560
and weigh your position carefully.

411
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:26,520
Looks like you really put in the effort.

412
00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:29,749
In principle, what you said isn't wrong.

413
00:16:29,750 --> 00:16:31,789
But don't just apply
the same language system

414
00:16:31,790 --> 00:16:34,269
you use in family court cases.

415
00:16:34,270 --> 00:16:35,119
That style

416
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:37,079
doesn't fit Ronghe.

417
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:38,909
We usually call this

418
00:16:38,910 --> 00:16:40,029
the Matthew effect,

419
00:16:40,030 --> 00:16:42,590
where the strong get stronger,
and strategic reciprocity.

420
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:45,710
The Matthew effect,
the strong get stronger.

421
00:16:46,030 --> 00:16:46,959
Alright, I understand.

422
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:48,470
I'll adjust.

423
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:52,909
Our firm regularly records courses
and forums for business schools.

424
00:16:52,910 --> 00:16:54,149
Next month's forum will be about

425
00:16:54,150 --> 00:16:55,599
the joint liability
of independent directors

426
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:57,350
in listed companies.

427
00:16:57,360 --> 00:16:59,669
The keynote speaker
is one of our senior partners.

428
00:16:59,670 --> 00:17:01,319
The guests attending the forum

429
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:03,629
are also important clients of our firm.

430
00:17:03,630 --> 00:17:05,119
You should come along
and get some exposure.

431
00:17:05,120 --> 00:17:06,270
Okay.

432
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:16,990
Judge Jiang,

433
00:17:17,230 --> 00:17:18,880
still working this late?

434
00:17:19,840 --> 00:17:22,079
See, I told you I'd go back
and keep you company,

435
00:17:22,080 --> 00:17:23,470
but you came over instead.

436
00:17:24,360 --> 00:17:25,989
I don't need you to keep me company.

437
00:17:25,990 --> 00:17:27,229
I came with Mr. He today

438
00:17:27,230 --> 00:17:28,879
for a symposium at the High Court

439
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:30,510
and stopped by to see you on the way.

440
00:17:30,670 --> 00:17:31,389
So you're planning

441
00:17:31,390 --> 00:17:33,519
to devote yourself
to our court building now?

442
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:35,599
Alright, let's go, I'll show you around.

443
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:37,429
This isn't the Forbidden City,
what's there to see?

444
00:17:37,430 --> 00:17:38,680
You go ahead with your work.

445
00:17:49,630 --> 00:17:51,200
So many cases lately.

446
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:52,750
My friend,

447
00:17:52,990 --> 00:17:54,429
if you need me to stay with you,

448
00:17:54,430 --> 00:17:56,559
I can go out for a drink with you.

449
00:17:56,560 --> 00:17:58,559
I don't need you to keep me company.

450
00:17:58,560 --> 00:18:01,119
I'm not a kid throwing a tantrum.

451
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:03,319
Just because I broke up, I don't
need a buddy to take me drinking.

452
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:04,149
That'd be embarrassing.

453
00:18:04,150 --> 00:18:05,640
It's not embarrassing, Shen Xiezhi.

454
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:07,799
A man is always a boy at heart.

455
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:09,189
Now that you've broken up,

456
00:18:09,190 --> 00:18:11,230
you're even more fragile, like a child.

457
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:13,989
Even if you feel like crying right now,
there's nothing embarrassing about it.

458
00:18:13,990 --> 00:18:16,039
Here, my shoulder's yours if you need it.

459
00:18:16,040 --> 00:18:16,879
Come on, cry.

460
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:18,600
- Go away.
- Come on, cry it out.

461
00:18:18,990 --> 00:18:20,559
You should get back to your work.

462
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:22,469
If you can't finish all these cases,

463
00:18:22,470 --> 00:18:24,839
your chief judge will be on your neck.

464
00:18:24,840 --> 00:18:26,310
Even if she comes after me, so be it.

465
00:18:26,390 --> 00:18:27,909
Today, you come first, brother.

466
00:18:27,910 --> 00:18:29,030
Let's go.

467
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:30,720
I'm not going to poach you
from your post.

468
00:18:30,720 --> 00:18:32,840
Just focus on your work,
do what you need to do.

469
00:18:33,710 --> 00:18:34,839
You sure?

470
00:18:34,840 --> 00:18:36,189
I'm sure.

471
00:18:36,190 --> 00:18:37,680
Just pretend I'm not here.

472
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:38,669
Go on, get to work.

473
00:18:38,670 --> 00:18:39,669
Then,

474
00:18:39,670 --> 00:18:40,629
I'll get back to work.

475
00:18:40,630 --> 00:18:42,120
Go ahead.

476
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:06,200
Do you remember,

477
00:19:06,430 --> 00:19:07,440
back in college,

478
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:09,839
during our sophomore internship at
the Beihai Intermediate People's Court,

479
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:11,149
when we were assigned into groups,

480
00:19:11,150 --> 00:19:13,120
the director at reception asked us

481
00:19:13,470 --> 00:19:14,989
which division we wanted to join?

482
00:19:14,990 --> 00:19:16,310
What did you say?

483
00:19:17,150 --> 00:19:18,710
Anywhere but the criminal division.

484
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:22,270
Back then, I really couldn't
stand that supervising counselor.

485
00:19:22,320 --> 00:19:23,839
(People's Court
Research and Investigation)

486
00:19:23,840 --> 00:19:25,989
I was the exact opposite of you.

487
00:19:25,990 --> 00:19:28,279
I said I wouldn't consider

488
00:19:28,280 --> 00:19:29,629
anything except the criminal division.

489
00:19:29,630 --> 00:19:30,950
And now,

490
00:19:31,470 --> 00:19:33,429
you've settled
into the criminal division,

491
00:19:33,430 --> 00:19:35,469
while I ended up in the family court.

492
00:19:35,470 --> 00:19:36,359
The family court

493
00:19:36,360 --> 00:19:39,470
is just one stage in your career.

494
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:42,629
Aren't you about to transfer
to the High Court and fight alongside me?

495
00:19:42,630 --> 00:19:44,160
What are you hesitating for?

496
00:19:44,470 --> 00:19:46,879
I didn't mean
that the family court is bad.

497
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:49,080
Back then, I just had issues

498
00:19:49,230 --> 00:19:51,790
with my dad making decisions for me.

499
00:19:53,190 --> 00:19:54,880
But honestly, lately,

500
00:19:54,990 --> 00:19:56,079
my experience in the family court

501
00:19:56,080 --> 00:19:57,790
has been quite valuable to me.

502
00:20:27,470 --> 00:20:28,389
Come on, praise me.

503
00:20:28,390 --> 00:20:30,599
I did something big today.

504
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:32,469
I connected my projector

505
00:20:32,470 --> 00:20:34,310
to my microscope.

506
00:20:34,710 --> 00:20:36,030
It nearly wore me out.

507
00:20:38,630 --> 00:20:40,160
So many books.

508
00:20:41,560 --> 00:20:43,790
Is this a marble pattern?

509
00:20:44,120 --> 00:20:45,750
You can project whatever you want.

510
00:20:45,760 --> 00:20:47,229
But don't project those bloody images

511
00:20:47,230 --> 00:20:48,599
onto the wall.

512
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:50,839
Understood, boss.

513
00:20:50,840 --> 00:20:52,279
Since I've received your favor,

514
00:20:52,280 --> 00:20:54,470
of course I'll do as you say.

515
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:58,550
But what you're calling a marble pattern

516
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:01,400
is actually from the surface
of the heart of a corpse.

517
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:03,600
What?

518
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:06,710
Don't talk about that at home.

519
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:08,519
Stop trying to scare me.

520
00:21:08,520 --> 00:21:10,680
I won't be able to sleep
after hearing that.

521
00:21:13,950 --> 00:21:14,759
Why did you

522
00:21:14,760 --> 00:21:17,360
bring back such
a huge pile of books today?

523
00:21:18,190 --> 00:21:19,359
Over the next month,

524
00:21:19,360 --> 00:21:20,799
I need to finish all of them.

525
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:21,989
(Organizational Optimization
Reform Project)

526
00:21:21,990 --> 00:21:22,559
Ms. Lou said

527
00:21:22,560 --> 00:21:24,790
I should attend an economic forum.

528
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:26,039
But I've never been to one,

529
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:28,360
and I don't really
understand this field.

530
00:21:28,430 --> 00:21:29,079
So I figured

531
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:31,189
I should study up on it.

532
00:21:31,190 --> 00:21:32,359
And I'm not even going with her.

533
00:21:32,360 --> 00:21:34,550
I'll be going with a lawyer surnamed Ye.

534
00:21:35,950 --> 00:21:39,030
I can't embarrass Ms. Lou.

535
00:21:39,520 --> 00:21:40,799
Our little Qin Rui

536
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:42,790
is really working hard.

537
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:46,079
My mom made braised pork,

538
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:47,550
which you can have
as a late-night snack.

539
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:49,600
You really do look out for me.

540
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:02,950
What kind of stuff
are you pushing to me?

541
00:22:03,910 --> 00:22:05,230
Go on, do your thing.

542
00:22:05,430 --> 00:22:06,750
Don't mind me.

543
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:10,119
My one true love is power.

544
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:13,440
I went through countless hardships
to conquer it.

545
00:22:13,910 --> 00:22:14,799
Don't even think

546
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:17,279
about anyone taking it away from me.

547
00:22:17,280 --> 00:22:18,759
Even if someone

548
00:22:18,760 --> 00:22:20,840
so much as casts
a covetous glance at it,

549
00:22:20,910 --> 00:22:22,640
it would pain me deeply.

550
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:24,230
Did...

551
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:26,750
Did Qin Shi Huang really say that?

552
00:22:27,230 --> 00:22:29,229
How could Qin Shi Huang
say something like that?

553
00:22:29,230 --> 00:22:32,030
These gossip bloggers
must've made it up.

554
00:22:32,910 --> 00:22:35,270
Qin Shi Huang was a great man.

555
00:22:35,430 --> 00:22:36,759
Besides,

556
00:22:36,760 --> 00:22:37,629
what's so out

557
00:22:37,630 --> 00:22:40,120
of character about that?

558
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:41,759
People say

559
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:43,429
he established the empress system,

560
00:22:43,430 --> 00:22:45,680
yet he never appointed
an empress in his lifetime.

561
00:22:46,630 --> 00:22:48,469
You seem pretty well-versed
in gossip history.

562
00:22:48,470 --> 00:22:49,879
Go on, get out of here.

563
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:51,840
What I admire about him

564
00:22:51,990 --> 00:22:53,920
isn't that he was the first emperor

565
00:22:54,230 --> 00:22:55,640
but that

566
00:22:55,710 --> 00:22:58,200
he created a new order.

567
00:22:59,080 --> 00:23:00,079
Without him,

568
00:23:00,080 --> 00:23:01,429
who knows how your name

569
00:23:01,430 --> 00:23:03,360
would even be written today.

570
00:23:10,990 --> 00:23:12,310
Done with work?

571
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:15,519
Let's grab a drink.

572
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:17,160
What did I just say?

573
00:23:18,910 --> 00:23:20,629
Why are you dragging things out?

574
00:23:20,630 --> 00:23:22,120
Don't cry later.

575
00:23:22,560 --> 00:23:23,669
Don't cry.

576
00:23:23,670 --> 00:23:25,750
Why would I cry? I didn't just break up.

577
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:27,200
Come on.

578
00:23:29,080 --> 00:23:30,120
Come on.

579
00:23:51,040 --> 00:23:52,360
Paper!

580
00:23:54,320 --> 00:23:55,359
You can't catch it.

581
00:23:55,360 --> 00:23:57,679
♪All the little things♪

582
00:23:57,680 --> 00:24:00,550
♪Woven into our lives♪

583
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:03,099
♪The building blocks of life♪

584
00:24:03,100 --> 00:24:04,919
♪Shape the sky above us♪

585
00:24:04,920 --> 00:24:07,339
♪Are you doing alright?♪

586
00:24:07,340 --> 00:24:10,350
♪What are you struggling for?♪

587
00:24:11,560 --> 00:24:13,230
(When you have someone you love)

588
00:24:13,390 --> 00:24:15,080
(by your side for life,)

589
00:24:15,990 --> 00:24:19,200
(even through storms and hardships,
you won't face them alone.)

590
00:24:19,910 --> 00:24:22,470
(You won't be afraid or lonely.)

591
00:24:23,190 --> 00:24:25,950
(He'll hold your hand and stand by you,)

592
00:24:27,360 --> 00:24:29,600
(and the two of you
can live happily ever after.)

593
00:24:30,150 --> 00:24:31,470
(How wonderful.)

594
00:24:34,920 --> 00:24:39,989
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

595
00:24:39,990 --> 00:24:41,120
(But)

596
00:24:41,670 --> 00:24:43,600
(choosing to become a great lawyer)

597
00:24:44,150 --> 00:24:46,229
(and truly finding
the career that suits me)

598
00:24:46,230 --> 00:24:46,949
(Business Cooperation Agreement)

599
00:24:46,950 --> 00:24:48,440
(and my calling)

600
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:51,400
(to pursue my dreams without regrets,)

601
00:24:52,150 --> 00:24:56,160
(isn't that the life I want too?)

602
00:24:58,060 --> 00:25:03,380
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

603
00:25:03,410 --> 00:25:07,450
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

604
00:25:07,650 --> 00:25:11,839
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

605
00:25:11,840 --> 00:25:14,510
(Qin Rui, you made the right choice.)

606
00:25:14,710 --> 00:25:16,400
(This is where you belong.)

607
00:25:16,760 --> 00:25:17,609
(You can't give up.)

608
00:25:17,610 --> 00:25:22,550
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

609
00:25:22,760 --> 00:25:25,000
(Economic Round-Table)

610
00:25:26,820 --> 00:25:32,109
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

611
00:25:32,110 --> 00:25:35,319
♪Where fairness stands♪

612
00:25:35,320 --> 00:25:36,629
(Ye Mingzhu,
Ronghe Law Firm, Senior Partner)

613
00:25:36,630 --> 00:25:37,149
Hello.

614
00:25:37,150 --> 00:25:38,680
Please show your invitation.

615
00:25:43,150 --> 00:25:44,400
You're good.

616
00:25:48,600 --> 00:25:50,440
(Economic Round-Table)

617
00:26:00,520 --> 00:26:01,229
Ma'am,

618
00:26:01,230 --> 00:26:02,909
the recording is about to begin.

619
00:26:02,910 --> 00:26:04,270
Please don't move around.

620
00:26:04,470 --> 00:26:06,189
It's fine, I'm here to deliver
something to Ms. Ye.

621
00:26:06,190 --> 00:26:07,149
I came with her.

622
00:26:07,150 --> 00:26:09,149
Sorry, the recording is about to begin.
Please take a seat here.

623
00:26:09,150 --> 00:26:11,320
Could you please make an exception?
I'll just leave it there and come right back.

624
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:12,039
No, this way please.

625
00:26:12,040 --> 00:26:15,519
- Please take your seats.
- Let's  welcome our distinguished guests.

626
00:26:15,520 --> 00:26:16,750
Welcome.

627
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:35,389
Hello.

628
00:26:35,390 --> 00:26:36,669
Welcome to today's

629
00:26:36,670 --> 00:26:38,359
Economic Round-Table.

630
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:39,949
First, allow me to introduce

631
00:26:39,950 --> 00:26:42,429
our distinguished guests.

632
00:26:42,430 --> 00:26:43,519
They are...

633
00:26:43,520 --> 00:26:45,799
Ms. Ye Mingzhu,

634
00:26:45,800 --> 00:26:46,949
Senior Partner at Ronghe Law Firm.

635
00:26:46,950 --> 00:26:48,230
Welcome.

636
00:26:49,700 --> 00:26:50,879
Mr. Ren Haiping, renowned economist

637
00:26:50,880 --> 00:26:53,149
and honorary director of
the Guowei Economic Research Center.

638
00:26:53,150 --> 00:26:55,030
Welcome.

639
00:26:59,040 --> 00:27:00,879
Professor Liang Jianhua,

640
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:03,510
economics professor
at Tianhai University. Welcome.

641
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:05,949
And finally,

642
00:27:05,950 --> 00:27:08,559
Mr. Wei Dong, the Chief Editor
of the Fengyun Finance program.

643
00:27:08,560 --> 00:27:09,840
Welcome.

644
00:27:12,390 --> 00:27:13,799
As you may know,

645
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:15,389
last November, the first instance judgment

646
00:27:15,390 --> 00:27:18,319
of the Jingren Pharmaceutical
securities dispute case came to a close.

647
00:27:18,320 --> 00:27:20,879
Five current
or former independent directors

648
00:27:20,880 --> 00:27:22,879
were held jointly liable

649
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:25,440
and ordered to pay 369 million yuan
in compensation.

650
00:27:25,990 --> 00:27:26,799
Ms. Ye,

651
00:27:26,800 --> 00:27:28,709
as a legal professional,

652
00:27:28,710 --> 00:27:30,750
what is your view on this?

653
00:27:32,280 --> 00:27:33,790
I believe...

654
00:27:39,630 --> 00:27:40,629
What's going on?

655
00:27:40,630 --> 00:27:42,360
Sound technician, please take a look.

656
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:45,840
Let me.

657
00:27:54,570 --> 00:27:55,989
These are the materials
I prepared for you.

658
00:27:55,990 --> 00:27:57,710
See if you can use them.

659
00:27:58,190 --> 00:27:59,510
Sorry about that.

660
00:28:02,360 --> 00:28:02,879
Alright.

661
00:28:02,880 --> 00:28:05,149
There was a small interruption just now.

662
00:28:05,150 --> 00:28:06,909
We will now continue.

663
00:28:06,910 --> 00:28:08,200
Ms. Ye,

664
00:28:08,430 --> 00:28:10,949
regarding your question about
the liability of independent directors,

665
00:28:10,950 --> 00:28:13,149
I think we can refer to

666
00:28:13,150 --> 00:28:15,559
the "Rules for Independent Directors
of Listed Companies"

667
00:28:15,560 --> 00:28:17,790
issued by the China Securities
Regulatory Commission on Jan 5, 2022...

668
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:26,909
You two stay close later.

669
00:28:26,910 --> 00:28:28,149
Pay attention to the details.

670
00:28:28,150 --> 00:28:28,709
Got it.

671
00:28:28,710 --> 00:28:29,149
Hello, ma'am.

672
00:28:29,150 --> 00:28:30,400
Are you here for the Round-Table?

673
00:28:30,400 --> 00:28:31,949
- Please sign in.
- That's not necessary, is it?

674
00:28:31,950 --> 00:28:32,319
Ma'am.

675
00:28:32,320 --> 00:28:33,389
What are you doing?

676
00:28:33,390 --> 00:28:34,279
Don't push.

677
00:28:34,280 --> 00:28:36,879
- Then, please show your invitation.
- What, not letting me in?

678
00:28:36,880 --> 00:28:39,839
We must approach this from
the institutional level of independent directors.

679
00:28:39,840 --> 00:28:40,879
Alright.

680
00:28:40,880 --> 00:28:41,949
Sorry,

681
00:28:41,950 --> 00:28:43,230
you can't go in.

682
00:28:47,520 --> 00:28:50,279
Mr. Ren, your wife, Ms. Bai, is here.
She's causing a scene at the entrance.

683
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:51,079
She's here?

684
00:28:51,080 --> 00:28:52,160
Yes.

685
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:54,200
Sorry.

686
00:28:55,760 --> 00:28:56,359
Um,

687
00:28:56,360 --> 00:28:58,559
the place where the guests
were resting just now...

688
00:28:58,560 --> 00:28:59,189
The lounge.

689
00:28:59,190 --> 00:29:00,790
- I'll take you there.
- Take me there, please.

690
00:29:02,710 --> 00:29:04,550
So without one I can't get in?

691
00:29:05,120 --> 00:29:06,229
Ma'am, you can't enter.

692
00:29:06,230 --> 00:29:07,119
This area is restricted.

693
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:08,149
Ren Haiping,

694
00:29:08,150 --> 00:29:09,229
are you feeling guilty?

695
00:29:09,230 --> 00:29:10,920
Why are you ducking when you see me?

696
00:29:12,190 --> 00:29:13,470
What are you doing?

697
00:29:14,080 --> 00:29:14,949
Get up.

698
00:29:14,950 --> 00:29:15,629
Ren Haiping!

699
00:29:15,630 --> 00:29:16,629
I've caught you now.

700
00:29:16,630 --> 00:29:17,669
Get out of here right now.

701
00:29:17,670 --> 00:29:19,599
Don't push her, she's my wife.

702
00:29:19,600 --> 00:29:22,550
Don't push her, don't grab her.

703
00:29:23,230 --> 00:29:24,710
Don't push her!

704
00:29:27,040 --> 00:29:27,839
Let go.

705
00:29:27,840 --> 00:29:28,879
Don't lay hands on her.

706
00:29:28,880 --> 00:29:30,019
Didn't I just tell you?

707
00:29:30,019 --> 00:29:32,119
She's my wife. I was shouting inside
until my voice went hoarse.

708
00:29:32,120 --> 00:29:33,680
Stop pretending here.

709
00:29:33,880 --> 00:29:35,750
Don't push forward.

710
00:29:36,760 --> 00:29:37,879
Wenjing,

711
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:39,799
can't this be discussed at home?

712
00:29:39,800 --> 00:29:41,120
No.

713
00:29:41,800 --> 00:29:43,909
Stop filming, stop filming.

714
00:29:43,910 --> 00:29:45,039
Stop filming, please.

715
00:29:45,040 --> 00:29:46,149
Between my wife and me,

716
00:29:46,150 --> 00:29:47,149
it's just some family matters,

717
00:29:47,150 --> 00:29:49,599
a few minor conflicts,
a small misunderstanding.

718
00:29:49,600 --> 00:29:51,189
What misunderstanding?

719
00:29:51,190 --> 00:29:52,080
What misunderstanding?

720
00:29:52,080 --> 00:29:53,519
If I hadn't checked Weibo
and seen the news,

721
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:55,629
I wouldn't even know you had
already come back to Tianhai.

722
00:29:55,630 --> 00:29:58,310
Last night, I was out of town,

723
00:29:58,360 --> 00:29:59,709
and the organizing committee called me,

724
00:29:59,710 --> 00:30:01,149
it was a last-minute notice

725
00:30:01,150 --> 00:30:01,989
asking me to attend.

726
00:30:01,990 --> 00:30:03,080
Ren Haiping,

727
00:30:03,150 --> 00:30:04,429
tell me the truth.

728
00:30:04,430 --> 00:30:06,200
Do you have another family outside?

729
00:30:06,950 --> 00:30:10,080
Me? Another family outside?

730
00:30:10,360 --> 00:30:11,039
Can you

731
00:30:11,040 --> 00:30:13,149
think like a normal woman for once?

732
00:30:13,150 --> 00:30:14,720
- Stop being so suspicious, alright?
- I am being normal.

733
00:30:14,720 --> 00:30:16,709
I'm not suspicious, I'm stating facts.

734
00:30:16,710 --> 00:30:17,559
You're not suspicious?

735
00:30:17,560 --> 00:30:18,189
I'm not.

736
00:30:18,190 --> 00:30:20,520
I was in meetings during the day.
Didn't I tell you I had meetings?

737
00:30:20,520 --> 00:30:21,879
Why did you insist on video calling me?

738
00:30:21,880 --> 00:30:24,359
I told you last night
that I had dinner with a leader tonight.

739
00:30:24,360 --> 00:30:25,599
And you asked me which leader.

740
00:30:25,600 --> 00:30:26,720
So I wasn't supposed to call?

741
00:30:26,720 --> 00:30:28,480
- Do you think we're teenagers?
- Don't I have that right?

742
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:30,079
We've been married for years.

743
00:30:30,080 --> 00:30:32,319
You're already a mother of three.

744
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:33,149
Ren Haiping.

745
00:30:33,150 --> 00:30:34,389
Wake up.

746
00:30:34,390 --> 00:30:35,629
Wake up?

747
00:30:35,630 --> 00:30:37,989
Do you know what it's called
when you don't come home?

748
00:30:37,990 --> 00:30:40,030
It's called de facto separation.

749
00:30:40,560 --> 00:30:41,949
You've really got a scheming mind.

750
00:30:41,950 --> 00:30:43,989
You really do.

751
00:30:43,990 --> 00:30:45,709
I'm telling you, enough.

752
00:30:45,710 --> 00:30:47,599
I'm not arguing with you.
I have a meeting today.

753
00:30:47,600 --> 00:30:48,839
I don't want to argue with you here.

754
00:30:48,840 --> 00:30:50,880
I don't want to argue, alright?

755
00:30:50,880 --> 00:30:52,359
You don't want
this marriage anymore, right?

756
00:30:52,360 --> 00:30:53,880
I don't want it either.

757
00:30:54,230 --> 00:30:55,440
You should've said so earlier.

758
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:56,989
You think I'm not as gentle
and pretty as other women?

759
00:30:56,990 --> 00:30:59,040
Now you're raising your hand?
All you know is hitting people.

760
00:30:59,040 --> 00:31:01,080
- What did I do?
- What's wrong with you?

761
00:31:56,080 --> 00:31:57,189
The mutton soup's here.

762
00:31:57,190 --> 00:31:58,709
This mutton soup is on the house.

763
00:31:58,710 --> 00:32:00,120
If you finish it, I'll refill it.

764
00:32:00,430 --> 00:32:01,429
Thanks, Mr. Lian.

765
00:32:01,430 --> 00:32:02,680
Thanks, Mr. Lian.

766
00:32:02,840 --> 00:32:04,189
Try

767
00:32:04,190 --> 00:32:05,709
our newly made chili oil.

768
00:32:05,710 --> 00:32:07,669
With mutton soup,

769
00:32:07,670 --> 00:32:09,319
it's incredibly fragrant.

770
00:32:09,320 --> 00:32:10,920
Let me try it.

771
00:32:18,150 --> 00:32:19,400
How is it?

772
00:32:21,390 --> 00:32:23,310
Xiezhi, let me give you an idea.

773
00:32:23,760 --> 00:32:24,759
Your family court

774
00:32:24,760 --> 00:32:26,359
should collaborate with Lian's place.

775
00:32:26,360 --> 00:32:27,759
Whenever people come for mediation,

776
00:32:27,760 --> 00:32:29,840
don't say anything, just give them
a bowl of mutton soup first.

777
00:32:30,040 --> 00:32:31,920
Once they drink a bowl,

778
00:32:32,390 --> 00:32:34,600
there's nothing left
worth arguing about.

779
00:32:34,910 --> 00:32:35,949
That's a great idea.

780
00:32:35,950 --> 00:32:37,319
What great idea?

781
00:32:37,320 --> 00:32:38,709
A bowl for each person?

782
00:32:38,710 --> 00:32:40,200
You want me to lose money?

783
00:32:40,280 --> 00:32:41,279
I'll pay you.

784
00:32:41,280 --> 00:32:43,440
Cut it out, just drink up.

785
00:32:43,440 --> 00:32:44,229
Call me when you're done.

786
00:32:44,230 --> 00:32:44,989
- Alright.
- Alright.

787
00:32:44,990 --> 00:32:45,669
Hello.

788
00:32:45,670 --> 00:32:46,759
Welcome to today's

789
00:32:46,760 --> 00:32:48,149
Economic Round-Table.

790
00:32:48,150 --> 00:32:49,759
First, allow me to introduce

791
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:52,189
our distinguished guests.

792
00:32:52,190 --> 00:32:53,229
They are...

793
00:32:53,230 --> 00:32:55,429
Ms. Ye Mingzhu,

794
00:32:55,430 --> 00:32:56,709
Senior Partner at Ronghe Law Firm.

795
00:32:56,710 --> 00:32:58,030
Welcome.

796
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:00,669
A renowned economist...

797
00:33:00,670 --> 00:33:02,470
Isn't that Lou Yue's colleague?

798
00:33:05,390 --> 00:33:06,559
How is your Lou Yue

799
00:33:06,560 --> 00:33:08,550
doing at Ronghe now?

800
00:33:09,230 --> 00:33:10,840
That's your Lou Yue.

801
00:33:12,040 --> 00:33:14,470
She's already a senior partner now.

802
00:33:15,080 --> 00:33:16,750
If I had known she'd do so well,

803
00:33:16,990 --> 00:33:19,230
I should've asked
for breakup compensation

804
00:33:19,390 --> 00:33:20,880
and taken a big chunk from her.

805
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:23,429
So every time she checks her balance,

806
00:33:23,430 --> 00:33:24,759
she'd think of me,

807
00:33:24,760 --> 00:33:25,879
never forget me.

808
00:33:25,880 --> 00:33:27,550
How can you be like that?

809
00:33:28,040 --> 00:33:30,640
She gave her youth for you too.

810
00:33:30,950 --> 00:33:33,030
Doesn't a man's youth count as youth?

811
00:33:33,320 --> 00:33:34,279
You know,

812
00:33:34,280 --> 00:33:36,440
back when she was preparing
for the bar exam,

813
00:33:36,560 --> 00:33:38,990
I woke up at five
every morning to save her a seat.

814
00:33:40,430 --> 00:33:41,279
Let me tell you,

815
00:33:41,280 --> 00:33:42,709
behind every successful woman,

816
00:33:42,710 --> 00:33:44,389
there's a successful man.

817
00:33:44,390 --> 00:33:46,400
And me? I'm even greater.

818
00:33:47,670 --> 00:33:51,080
I was the stepping stone
that sent her to the top.

819
00:33:51,520 --> 00:33:52,909
Stop being so full of yourself.

820
00:33:52,910 --> 00:33:56,120
You're already just
a former stepping stone now.

821
00:34:00,390 --> 00:34:01,879
Alright, stop watching.

822
00:34:01,880 --> 00:34:02,599
Turn it off.

823
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:03,759
Alright.

824
00:34:03,760 --> 00:34:05,440
Look, look over there, who is that?

825
00:34:07,990 --> 00:34:10,509
Professor Liang Jianhua, economics professor
at Tianhai University.

826
00:34:10,510 --> 00:34:12,830
That's the real person.

827
00:34:15,590 --> 00:34:17,350
I almost didn't recognize him.

828
00:34:41,430 --> 00:34:43,359
You seem pretty content
just cooking mutton soup.

829
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:44,909
Even got background music.

830
00:34:44,910 --> 00:34:45,639
You're here.

831
00:34:45,640 --> 00:34:47,159
This pot will be ready soon.

832
00:34:47,160 --> 00:34:48,909
Alright, let someone else handle it.

833
00:34:48,910 --> 00:34:50,989
Go change your clothes,
I'll drive you there.

834
00:34:50,990 --> 00:34:51,839
Drive?

835
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:53,029
Where to?

836
00:34:53,030 --> 00:34:55,270
To see Fan, did you forget?

837
00:34:56,720 --> 00:34:59,239
I actually forgot to tell you, I arranged to
meet him at the mutton soup shop.

838
00:34:59,240 --> 00:35:00,640
He'll be here soon.

839
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:01,909
Why meet here?

840
00:35:01,910 --> 00:35:03,710
It's so noisy, how can you talk?

841
00:35:04,100 --> 00:35:05,759
If you want quiet,
there are private rooms upstairs.

842
00:35:05,760 --> 00:35:06,839
Those are quiet.

843
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:08,069
Quiet, sure,

844
00:35:08,070 --> 00:35:10,230
but there's still that mutton smell.

845
00:35:10,990 --> 00:35:13,680
So what about the smell?

846
00:35:14,470 --> 00:35:15,790
Are you saying

847
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:17,069
I'm embarrassing you

848
00:35:17,070 --> 00:35:18,509
or that I don't match

849
00:35:18,510 --> 00:35:20,640
your dignity as a legal professional?

850
00:35:21,550 --> 00:35:23,429
Alright, I won't argue with you.

851
00:35:23,430 --> 00:35:24,910
Just go change your clothes.

852
00:35:25,360 --> 00:35:27,830
I even brought you some perfume.
Spray some, get rid of the smell.

853
00:35:27,840 --> 00:35:28,960
I'm not changing.

854
00:35:29,390 --> 00:35:30,759
Just change, will you?

855
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:33,319
At least show some respect
when talking business.

856
00:35:33,320 --> 00:35:34,909
I was just about to talk
to you about that.

857
00:35:34,910 --> 00:35:36,159
This meeting

858
00:35:36,160 --> 00:35:37,790
is mainly just catching up.

859
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:39,910
I don't want that job.

860
00:35:40,240 --> 00:35:41,589
Why not?

861
00:35:41,590 --> 00:35:43,200
It's such a rare opportunity.

862
00:35:43,470 --> 00:35:45,029
Let me say it again,

863
00:35:45,030 --> 00:35:47,480
this job doesn't suit our family.

864
00:35:47,720 --> 00:35:49,429
You're worried
about business trips, right?

865
00:35:49,430 --> 00:35:51,839
I already told you
I can accommodate you.

866
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:53,270
Some things,

867
00:35:53,390 --> 00:35:54,389
once they start,

868
00:35:54,390 --> 00:35:56,319
you won't have a choice anymore.

869
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:57,199
Besides,

870
00:35:57,200 --> 00:35:59,279
after all these years, I'm used to it.

871
00:35:59,280 --> 00:36:01,040
I really don't want to make a change.

872
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:02,679
What do you mean
you don't want to change?

873
00:36:02,680 --> 00:36:03,949
You've read so many books,

874
00:36:03,950 --> 00:36:05,549
just to wash lamb here?

875
00:36:05,550 --> 00:36:07,469
You stayed up night
after night memorizing legal codes,

876
00:36:07,470 --> 00:36:08,639
just to soak them in mutton soup

877
00:36:08,640 --> 00:36:10,200
like vermicelli?

878
00:36:11,910 --> 00:36:13,589
Do you think staying in this shop

879
00:36:13,590 --> 00:36:15,120
means I've given up on myself?

880
00:36:15,640 --> 00:36:16,799
Let me tell you,

881
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:18,679
I'm enjoying my life right now.

882
00:36:18,680 --> 00:36:19,949
Enjoying what?

883
00:36:19,950 --> 00:36:21,389
Don't think I don't know.

884
00:36:21,390 --> 00:36:22,799
The night Chief Judge Xu retired,

885
00:36:22,800 --> 00:36:24,750
you got drunk and threw up everywhere.

886
00:36:25,430 --> 00:36:26,549
I know you want to go back.

887
00:36:26,550 --> 00:36:27,799
I know you're not at peace with it.

888
00:36:27,800 --> 00:36:29,509
But I don't know what you're afraid of.

889
00:36:29,510 --> 00:36:31,239
Are you afraid people will laugh at you?

890
00:36:31,240 --> 00:36:33,389
If you go back openly
and work in legal practice again,

891
00:36:33,390 --> 00:36:35,279
you can still make a comeback.

892
00:36:35,280 --> 00:36:37,520
Why do you insist on staying here?

893
00:36:38,110 --> 00:36:40,480
So who is it that's afraid
of being looked down on?

894
00:36:40,550 --> 00:36:42,830
Who cares that I used to sell lamb?

895
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:46,200
It's you, isn't it?

896
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:54,279
I'll say it again,

897
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:55,239
being here

898
00:36:55,240 --> 00:36:57,040
doesn't make me uncomfortable at all.

899
00:36:57,510 --> 00:36:59,359
If you can't accept it, fine.

900
00:36:59,360 --> 00:37:01,389
Do as you like.
I'll go along with you, alright?

901
00:37:01,390 --> 00:37:03,350
- Then go change your clothes.
- I'm not changing!

902
00:37:24,550 --> 00:37:26,319
For allocable resources,

903
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:28,159
when shifting them

904
00:37:28,160 --> 00:37:30,750
from one allocation state to another,

905
00:37:31,280 --> 00:37:32,239
without

906
00:37:32,240 --> 00:37:35,989
making anyone worse off,

907
00:37:35,990 --> 00:37:38,509
while making at least
one person better off,

908
00:37:38,510 --> 00:37:40,719
that is called a Pareto improvement

909
00:37:40,720 --> 00:37:43,040
or Pareto optimality.

910
00:38:06,200 --> 00:38:07,560
Does it hurt?

911
00:38:09,070 --> 00:38:11,679
I looked away for one second
and this happened.

912
00:38:11,680 --> 00:38:12,509
Seriously.

913
00:38:12,510 --> 00:38:14,710
Your phone fell into the pot
and you grabbed it with your hand?

914
00:38:14,800 --> 00:38:16,040
Silly.

915
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:17,759
It wasn't on purpose,

916
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:19,310
just instinct.

917
00:38:19,880 --> 00:38:22,430
You ended up like this
just memorizing terms?

918
00:38:22,510 --> 00:38:24,469
Are you even studying properly?

919
00:38:24,470 --> 00:38:26,230
It'll be fine soon.

920
00:38:26,590 --> 00:38:28,200
Look, I'll cool it down

921
00:38:29,160 --> 00:38:30,480
by putting it in my mouth.

922
00:38:31,240 --> 00:38:32,560
It'll be fine in a bit.

923
00:38:35,990 --> 00:38:38,390
You were distracted, right?
What were you thinking about?

924
00:38:40,910 --> 00:38:42,600
Thinking about Shen Xiezhi?

925
00:38:48,640 --> 00:38:49,910
So yes?

926
00:38:52,840 --> 00:38:54,160
Regret it?

927
00:38:55,720 --> 00:38:57,270
Not really regret.

928
00:38:58,320 --> 00:38:59,029
At that time,

929
00:38:59,030 --> 00:39:01,870
I happened to be reading
about economics,

930
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:04,589
and it actually made sense.

931
00:39:04,590 --> 00:39:05,719
Look.

932
00:39:05,720 --> 00:39:08,069
Economic theory?

933
00:39:08,070 --> 00:39:10,469
Two people, A and B,

934
00:39:10,470 --> 00:39:13,600
at least one of them becomes better off,

935
00:39:13,840 --> 00:39:16,029
while neither is worse off,

936
00:39:16,030 --> 00:39:17,870
only then can it be considered

937
00:39:18,030 --> 00:39:21,120
Pareto optimal.

938
00:39:23,720 --> 00:39:25,160
What are you talking about?

939
00:39:27,720 --> 00:39:29,069
What does that even mean?

940
00:39:29,070 --> 00:39:31,230
Isn't that just Shen Xiezhi and me?

941
00:39:31,910 --> 00:39:33,680
Some relationships
would be better left undone

942
00:39:34,160 --> 00:39:35,949
if being together would make

943
00:39:35,950 --> 00:39:38,040
the other person worse off.

944
00:39:39,030 --> 00:39:40,560
Stop pretending.

945
00:39:41,720 --> 00:39:44,319
You're just going through a phase.

946
00:39:44,320 --> 00:39:45,319
It's normal.

947
00:39:45,320 --> 00:39:46,589
That's why people say,

948
00:39:46,590 --> 00:39:48,230
without love, life feels lighter.

949
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:51,080
All love comes with regrets.

950
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:53,870
That's what makes it unforgettable.

951
00:39:56,240 --> 00:39:58,000
Alright, I'll go with you.

952
00:40:05,950 --> 00:40:07,120
Come on in.

953
00:40:08,160 --> 00:40:08,719
Ms. Lou.

954
00:40:08,720 --> 00:40:09,910
Come.

955
00:40:12,240 --> 00:40:13,509
Mr. Ren,

956
00:40:13,510 --> 00:40:15,429
this is my special assistant, Qin Rui.

957
00:40:15,430 --> 00:40:17,680
She specializes
in family cases under me.

958
00:40:18,320 --> 00:40:19,509
Hello, Mr. Ren.

959
00:40:19,510 --> 00:40:20,389
Hello.

960
00:40:20,390 --> 00:40:22,589
She has handled
many family cases before.

961
00:40:22,590 --> 00:40:24,199
She has ideas and ability.

962
00:40:24,200 --> 00:40:25,989
Your divorce case

963
00:40:25,990 --> 00:40:26,989
will be handled by her.

964
00:40:26,990 --> 00:40:28,160
Alright.

965
00:40:28,390 --> 00:40:30,159
Since Ms. Qin comes
so highly recommended

966
00:40:30,160 --> 00:40:31,879
by Ms. Lou and Ms. Ye,

967
00:40:31,880 --> 00:40:34,230
she must have something exceptional.

968
00:40:35,160 --> 00:40:37,080
I look forward to your performance.

969
00:40:37,240 --> 00:40:38,310
Thank you.

970
00:40:40,990 --> 00:40:42,839
Mr. Ren specifically
asked me to assist you

971
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:44,429
with all matters
regarding the divorce case.

972
00:40:44,430 --> 00:40:46,870
According to your requirements,
I've prepared some materials.

973
00:40:46,950 --> 00:40:48,560
These are Mr. Ren's equity records.

974
00:40:50,470 --> 00:40:52,200
These are his bank statements.

975
00:40:53,470 --> 00:40:55,680
These are his tax records
over the years.

976
00:40:55,990 --> 00:40:56,679
And these

977
00:40:56,680 --> 00:40:58,069
are his property records,

978
00:40:58,070 --> 00:40:59,800
(Purchase Contract)
as well as real estate documentation,

979
00:40:59,800 --> 00:41:02,799
along with transfer receipts
and contract copies.

980
00:41:02,800 --> 00:41:04,200
Please take a look.

981
00:41:06,280 --> 00:41:07,400
(Purchase Contract)

982
00:41:07,760 --> 00:41:09,560
Thank you, this is quite comprehensive.

983
00:41:10,800 --> 00:41:12,109
I remember

984
00:41:12,110 --> 00:41:13,359
during the Economic Round-Table,

985
00:41:13,360 --> 00:41:15,069
Ms. Bai mentioned

986
00:41:15,070 --> 00:41:16,480
a secretary surnamed Liu.

987
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:17,909
Just in case,

988
00:41:17,910 --> 00:41:19,069
Mr. Ren specifically instructed

989
00:41:19,070 --> 00:41:19,639
that Liu

990
00:41:19,640 --> 00:41:21,589
print out all her chat records

991
00:41:21,590 --> 00:41:23,000
with him over the past three years.

992
00:41:23,240 --> 00:41:24,549
Anything involving company secrets

993
00:41:24,550 --> 00:41:25,429
has been redacted.

994
00:41:25,430 --> 00:41:27,389
If any part of the conversation
can serve as evidence,

995
00:41:27,390 --> 00:41:28,870
she can later provide the originals.

996
00:41:28,950 --> 00:41:30,509
If you have any questions for Liu,

997
00:41:30,510 --> 00:41:32,159
Mr. Ren arranged
for her to work overtime today.

998
00:41:32,160 --> 00:41:33,199
She's been briefed in advance

999
00:41:33,200 --> 00:41:35,350
to fully cooperate
with all your requests.

1000
00:41:36,680 --> 00:41:37,679
I'd like to ask,

1001
00:41:37,680 --> 00:41:38,879
is there anyone in the company

1002
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:41,069
who is close to both Mr. Ren

1003
00:41:41,070 --> 00:41:42,279
and Ms. Bai

1004
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:44,000
and understands their relationship well?

1005
00:41:45,160 --> 00:41:46,989
Liu has been with Mr. Ren longer.

1006
00:41:46,990 --> 00:41:48,549
She should know more.

1007
00:41:48,550 --> 00:41:48,989
Alright.

1008
00:41:48,990 --> 00:41:50,799
Then please have her come in.

1009
00:41:50,800 --> 00:41:52,640
Okay, please wait a moment.

1010
00:41:52,680 --> 00:41:53,830
Thank you.

1011
00:42:08,070 --> 00:42:10,680
(Money can really smooth things over.)

1012
00:42:11,470 --> 00:42:13,589
(Even something as troubling as divorce)

1013
00:42:13,590 --> 00:42:16,040
(can be made to look almost pleasant.)

1014
00:42:39,070 --> 00:42:39,799
Your Honor,

1015
00:42:39,800 --> 00:42:41,759
we've brought Song Chenghao here.

1016
00:42:41,760 --> 00:42:43,029
Alright, thank you, Miss.

1017
00:42:43,030 --> 00:42:44,109
You're welcome.

1018
00:42:44,110 --> 00:42:45,390
You can talk first.

1019
00:42:46,280 --> 00:42:47,799
Please close the door for us.

1020
00:42:47,800 --> 00:42:48,359
Okay.

1021
00:42:48,360 --> 00:42:50,000
Come, have a seat.

1022
00:42:56,320 --> 00:42:57,719
Your name is Song Chenghao, right?

1023
00:42:57,720 --> 00:42:58,199
Yes.

1024
00:42:58,200 --> 00:43:00,759
Alright, who would you like
to live with going forward?

1025
00:43:00,760 --> 00:43:01,949
Let's hear your thoughts.

1026
00:43:01,950 --> 00:43:03,029
Alright.

1027
00:43:03,030 --> 00:43:04,160
Alright.

1028
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

1029
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

1030
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

1031
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1032
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1033
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1034
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

1035
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

1036
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

1037
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

1038
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

1039
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1040
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1041
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1042
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

1043
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

1044
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

1045
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

1046
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

1047
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

1048
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

1049
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

1050
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

1051
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

1052
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

1053
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:44,590
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1054
00:44:44,590 --> 00:44:47,040
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1055
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:49,150
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1056
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:51,530
♪Some questions♪

1057
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,800
♪Weigh like mountains♪

1058
00:44:57,690 --> 00:45:02,840
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1059
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:07,130
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1060
00:45:07,310 --> 00:45:12,360
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1061
00:45:12,730 --> 00:45:16,430
♪Where fairness stands♪

1062
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:19,680
♪Within the law♪

1063
00:45:20,840 --> 00:45:29,520
♪And within every heart♪
